This paper proposes a deep neuroevolution model for cooperative intelligent freeway traffic control, which involves the use of graph convolutional networks and knowledge sharing layers for communication between different agents. The paper also addresses issues such as delayed reward and action asynchronism through the use of evolutionary strategy. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
